The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Friday, July 01, 2005 

 IN THE CITY

 Former India international Anita Sarkar has been selected for the two-month international DFB coaches? training programme in Germany from August 29. The training programme will continue till October 28. Anita has already completed level A in coaching and is the first woman in the world with FA advanced licence. 

 About 400 footballers are expected to undergo the training. She received the letter on Tuesday and is now looking for sponsorship avenues. 

 Mohun Bagan are likely to do a pre-season training camp from Monday in Salt Lake, while two other city giants East Bengal and Mohammedan Sporting will start training on Friday. 

 Habibur Rahman Mondal withdrew in favour of East Bengal on Thursday. 

 FOOTBALL: CFL third and fifth division matches at various grounds from 4 pm.




